        "QuestionNumber": 3,
        "QuestionType": "Structured Question",
        "Level": "P1",
        "MathTopic": "Binomial Expansion",
        "TopicsCovered": [
            "Binomial Theorem",
            "Expansion",
            "Coefficient Calculation"
        ],
        "MarksAllocation": {
            "PartA": 2,
            "PartB": 2,
            "PartC": 2,
            "TotalMarks": 6
        },
        "DifficultyLevel": "Moderate",
        "ImageUrl": [
            "/9709_P1_2022_Nov_13/q3.png"
        ]
    },
    "QuestionContent": {
        "Parts": [
            {
                "Part": "a",
                "Text": "Find the first three terms in ascending powers of \\(x\\) of the expansion of \\((1 + 2x)^5\\)."
            },
            {
                "Part": "b",
                "Text": "Find the first three terms in ascending powers of \\(x\\) of the expansion of \\((1 - 3x)^4\\)."
            },
            {
                "Part": "c",
                "Text": "Hence find the coefficient of \\(x^2\\) in the expansion of \\((1 + 2x)^5 (1 - 3x)^4\\)."
            }
        ]
    },
    "SolutionContent": {
        "Parts": [
            {
                "Part": "a",
                "Solution": [
                    "Using the binomial expansion for \\((1 + 2x)^5\\):",
                    "\\[1 + \\binom{5}{1}(2x) + \\binom{5}{2}(2x)^2 + \\dots\\]",
                    "\\[= 1 + 10x + 40x^2 + \\dots\\].",
                    "Thus, the first three terms are \\(1 + 10x + 40x^2\\)."
                ],
                "MarkingScheme": {
                    "B2": "Correct first three terms (1 + 10x + 40x^2).",
                    "B1": "Partially correct expansion."
                }
            },
            {
                "Part": "b",
                "Solution": [
                    "Using the binomial expansion for \\((1 - 3x)^4\\):",
                    "\\[1 + \\binom{4}{1}(-3x) + \\binom{4}{2}(-3x)^2 + \\dots\\]",
                    "\\[= 1 - 12x + 54x^2 + \\dots\\].",
                    "Thus, the first three terms are \\(1 - 12x + 54x^2\\)."
                ],
                "MarkingScheme": {
                    "B2": "Correct first three terms (1 - 12x + 54x^2).",
                    "B1": "Partially correct expansion."
                }
            },
            {
                "Part": "c",
                "Solution": [
                    "Multiply the expansions from (a) and (b) and find the coefficient of \\(x^2\\):",
                    "\\( (1 + 10x + 40x^2)(1 - 12x + 54x^2) \\)",
                    "For \\(x^2\\), the relevant terms are:",
                    "\\[1 \\cdot 54x^2,\\]",
                    "\\[10x \\cdot (-12x),\\]",
                    "\\[40x^2 \\cdot 1.\\]",
                    "Add the coefficients: \\(54 - 120 + 40 = -26\\).",
                    "Thus, the coefficient of \\(x^2\\) is \\(-26\\)."
                ],
                "MarkingScheme": {
                    "M1": "Correct multiplication of relevant terms.",
                    "A1": "Correct final coefficient \\(-26\\)."
                }
            }
        ],
        "FinalAnswer": {
            "PartA": "First three terms: \\(1 + 10x + 40x^2\\)",
            "PartB": "First three terms: \\(1 - 12x + 54x^2\\)",
            "PartC": "Coefficient of \\(x^2\\): \\(-26\\)"
        }
    }
},
{
    "Metadata": {
        "QuestionTitle": "Rate of Change of Depth",
        "Source": "Cambridge International AS & A Level Mathematics: Pure Mathematics 1 Past Paper",
        "ExamBoard": "CAIE",
        "SyllabusCode": "9709",
        "Subject": "MATH",
        "YearOfExam": 2022,
        "Session": "October/November",
        "PaperNumber": "Paper 1",
        "QuestionNumber": 4,
        "QuestionType": "Structured Question",
        "Level": "P1",
        "MathTopic": "Rates of Change",
        "TopicsCovered": [
            "Differentiation",
            "Chain Rule"
        ],
        "MarksAllocation": {
            "PartA": 5
        },
        "DifficultyLevel": "Moderate",
        "ImageUrl": [
            "/9709_P1_2022_Nov_13/q4.png"
        ]
    },
    "QuestionContent": {
        "Parts": [],
        "Text": "A large industrial water tank is such that, when the depth of the water in the tank is \\(x\\) metres, the volume \\(V \\text{ m}^3\\) of water in the tank is given by \\(V = 243 - \\frac{1}{3}(9 - x)^3\\). Water is being pumped into the tank at a constant rate of \\(3.6 \\text{ m}^3 \\text{ per hour}\\).\n\nFind the rate of increase of the depth of the water when the depth is \\(4 \\text{ m}\\), giving your answer in \\(\\text{cm per minute}\\)."
    },
    "SolutionContent": {
        "Parts": [
            {
                "Part": "a",
                "Solution": "\\[ \\frac{dV}{dx} = (9 - x)^2 \\]\n\nSubstitute \\(x = 4\\) into \\(\\frac{dV}{dx}\\):\n\\[ \\frac{dV}{dx} = (9 - 4)^2 = 25 \\]\n\nUsing the chain rule:\n\\[ \\frac{dx}{dt} = \\frac{1}{\\frac{dV}{dx}} \\times \\frac{dV}{dt} \\]\n\\[ \\frac{dx}{dt} = \\frac{1}{25} \\times 3.6 \\]\n\\[ \\frac{dx}{dt} = 0.144 \\text{ m/hr} \\]\n\nConvert \\(\\text{m/hr}\\) to \\(\\text{cm/min}\\):\n\\[ \\frac{dx}{dt} = 0.144 \\times 100 \\div 60 \\]\n\\[ \\frac{dx}{dt} = 0.24 \\text{ cm/min} \\]",
                "MarkingScheme": "B1 for \\(\\frac{dV}{dx} = (9 - x)^2\\). M1 for chain rule applied correctly to find \\(\\frac{dx}{dt}\\). M1 for correct use of conversion factors. A1 for \\(0.24 \\text{ cm/min}\\)."
            }
        ]
    }
},
