        "Subject": "MATH",
        "YearOfExam": 2022,
        "Session": "October/November",
        "PaperNumber": "Paper 1",
        "QuestionNumber": 6,
        "QuestionType": "Structured Question",
        "Level": "P1",
        "MathTopic": "Trigonometry",
        "TopicsCovered": [
            "Trigonometric Ratios",
            "Exact Values"
        ],
        "MarksAllocation": 5,
        "DifficultyLevel": "Moderate",
        "ImageUrl": "/9709_P1_2022_Nov_13/q6.png"
    },
    "QuestionContent": {
        "Parts": [],
        "Text": "It is given that \\( \\alpha = \\cos^{-1}\\left(\\frac{8}{17}\\right) \\).\n\nFind, without using the trigonometric functions on your calculator, the exact value of \\( \\frac{1}{\\sin \\alpha} + \\frac{1}{\\tan \\alpha} \\)."
    },
    "SolutionContent": {
        "Parts": [
            {
                "Part": "a",
                "Solution": "Using \\( \\sin^2 \\alpha + \\cos^2 \\alpha = 1 \\), we calculate \\( \\sin \\alpha = \\pm \\sqrt{1 - \\cos^2 \\alpha} = \\pm \\sqrt{1 - \\left(\\frac{8}{17}\\right)^2} \\).\n\nFrom \\( \\cos \\alpha = \\frac{8}{17} \\), we find:\n\\( \\sin \\alpha = \\frac{15}{17} \\), \\( \\tan \\alpha = \\frac{\\sin \\alpha}{\\cos \\alpha} = \\frac{15}{8} \\).\n\nNow calculate:\n\\[ \\frac{1}{\\sin \\alpha} + \\frac{1}{\\tan \\alpha} = \\frac{17}{15} + \\frac{8}{15} = \\frac{25}{15} = \\frac{5}{3}. \\]",
                "MarkingScheme": {
                    "B1": "For correctly using \\( \\sin^2 \\alpha + \\cos^2 \\alpha = 1 \\).",
                    "A1": "For finding \\( \\sin \\alpha = \\frac{15}{17} \\).",
                    "A1": "For finding \\( \\tan \\alpha = \\frac{15}{8} \\).",
                    "DM1": "For correctly using reciprocals and simplifying \\( \\frac{1}{\\sin \\alpha} + \\frac{1}{\\tan \\alpha} \\).",
                    "A1": "For the final answer \\( \\frac{5}{3} \\)."
                }
            }
        ]
    }
},
